word_group.brief_definition: 精彩的表演；无与伦比的表演；扣人心弦的表演

bilingual.source: She wore a fabulous dress to the party.
bilingual.target: 她穿了一件极好的裙子去参加聚会。

bilingual.source: His performance in the play was fabulous.
bilingual.target: 他在戏剧中的表演极好。

bilingual.source: They had a fabulous time on their vacation.
bilingual.target: 他们在度假时度过了极好的时光。

bilingual.source: The food at that restaurant is simply fabulous.
bilingual.target: 那家餐厅的食物简直极好。

bilingual.source: The view from the top of the mountain is fabulous.
bilingual.target: 从山顶看到的景色极好。
是啊，你看上去气色真好！
蜂车是一种神话般的车。
但这本书却写得十分精彩。
他成了一个传说性的人物。

list.abstract: 《Fabulous》是电视原声的音乐作品，收录在《Non-Stop Dance Party》专辑中。

yingyinNormal.en: It is a fabulous dress for the premiere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 做首映式礼服简直无敌了。

yingyinNormal.en: Not yet, but I'm sure it'll all be fabulous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 还没，不过我担保都会是赞扬之声的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, there'll be other reviews, fabulous reviews.
yingyinNormal.zh: 肯定会有人给出好的评价的。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, where are these fabulous copies? I don't see them anywhere.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗯，那么装订好的两本手稿在哪呢？，我怎么没看到？

yingyinNormal.en: So Carrie, how's the writing going? Still working for Vogue? Freelance. Oh, that's fabulous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你的写作怎么样了？还在《时尚》吗？自由职业，真棒。

yingyinNormal.en: Louis XVI wore a fabulous stone called the Blue Diamond of the Crown. It disappeared in 1792.
yingyinNormal.zh: 路易十六世有颗"王冠碧钻"，在一七九二年时不见了。

yingyinNormal.en: Joey, sweetheart, you were fabulous. Hey you guys, this is my agent, Estelle. How do you do. Hi.
yingyinNormal.zh: 乔伊宝贝，你太棒了。各位，这是我的经纪人艾斯黛。你们好。

yingyinNormal.en: You tiny thing. In the face of the fabulous new, your only thought is to kill it? For fear of great change?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你这弱小的人类。遇到新事物，你就一心想着扼杀它？害怕发生巨变？

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, this lipstick looks just great on you. You look fabulous honey, you really do. Yeah? Are you sure, really?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你擦上这口红真美。你美呆了，真的。你们确定吗？真的吗？

yingyinNormal.en: You mean these tuxes have been down the red carpet with people yelling, "Who are you wearing? You look fabulous."
yingyinNormal.zh: 它们都上过红地毯，被人叫着：“你穿的是谁的？你看来棒极了。”

yingyinNormal.en: So, listen, if you were looking for some clothes for work, Nordstrom's having a fabulous sale. I picked up this appropriate little number there.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你想买一些上班时穿的衣服，诺德斯特姆在搞大减价呢，我在那里选了这件得体的小码衣服。

yingyinNormal.en: Over the decades many New Yorkers made it big, and much of that fabulous wealth was reinvested into collecting some of the greatest artworks on the planet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 几十年以来，很多纽约民众为使这个公园变得更精彩丰富，再次投放大量资金来收集世界上最伟大的艺术作品。

yingyinNormal.en: Imagine you were faced with the choice of having a safe, boring life if you stay where you are, or having a fabulous one if you take the risk of successfully crossing a dangerous jungle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 想象你正面临着两个选择，要么止步不前，过波澜不惊的无聊生活；要么冒险穿过危险的丛林，过精彩的生活。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。
